  ],
  "description": "The subspring network model can be used to simulate unbonded and bonded systems. Like the Spring Network Model, the bonded formulation is based on the Rigid Body Spring Network (RBSN) lattice model introduced by [Bolander1998] based on the work of [Kawai1978] .",
  "typical_applications": [
    "Sub-spring network fracture (refined RBSN)",
    "Quasi-brittle fracture with sub-spring discretization",
    "Heterogeneous strength via tables"
  ],
